      <div class="story community-engagement-section landscape-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2019/02/apple-1-600x401.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/college-podcasts-compete-in-wfae-contest/" title="College Podcasts Compete In WFAE Contest">
          College Podcasts Compete In WFAE Contest
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         February 15, 2019 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          The UNC Charlotte Botanical Gardens produces the podcast “The Plants We Eat.” English professor Alan Rauch has created “Air-udition.” Both are entries in the Queen City PodQuest, sponsored by NPR affiliate WFAE.
