      <h2>
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/ink/" title="INK Archives">
        INK
       </a>
      </h2>
      <div class="story ink-section portrait-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2019/02/goldfield-ps-1-400x600.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/college-authors-explore-tenets-of-government-to-educate-and-inform/" title="College Authors Explore Tenets Of Government, To Educate And Inform">
          College Authors Explore Tenets Of Government, To Educate And Inform
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         February 05, 2019 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          From an unprecedented look at what has been called the Gifted Generation, to a behind the scenes review of the costs and benefits of hosting major political party conventions, to an exploration of the factors that prompt citizens to reject public policies that appear to give them exactly what they want, College of Liberal Arts &amp; Sciences faculty have published an array of books that pull back the curtain on government topics that affect citizens’ lives.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
