   <div class="widget widget_section_listing" id="section_listing-8">
    <div class="wscontrol section-listing-control" id="section-listing-control-13">
     <div class="section-box global-reach-section landscape-image">
      <h2>
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/global-reach/" title="GLOBAL REACH Archives">
        GLOBAL REACH
       </a>
      </h2>
      <div class="story global-reach-section landscape-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2018/11/Tanure-Ojaide-2018-2-600x401.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/heart-and-home-writer-challenges-inspires-with-his-words/" title="Heart and Home: Writer Challenges, Inspires With His Words">
          Heart and Home: Writer Challenges, Inspires With His Words
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         December 18, 2018 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          In his 2017 memoir At Home, Away From Home, UNC Charlotte’s Tanure Ojaide speaks of the indelible impressions from his early years in Nigeria. In his words, “One does not forget what one yearns for at heart.” At age 70, many of his poems, short stories, critical essays, and books serve as activist works calling out for justice and fairness for the people and the ecosystem of the Niger Delta.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
      <!-- .post -->
