   <div class="widget widget_section_listing" id="section_listing-15">
    <div class="wscontrol section-listing-control" id="section-listing-control-14">
     <div class="section-box teaching-advising-section landscape-image">
      <h2>
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/teaching-and-advising/" title="TEACHING &amp; ADVISING Archives">
        TEACHING &amp; ADVISING
       </a>
      </h2>
      <div class="story teaching-advising-section landscape-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2019/02/Culture-Blocks-Clayworks-Workshop-@-Hickory-Grove-Library-4-15-17-by-Jon-Strayhorn-025-600x399.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/mpa-capstone-project-to-assess-impact-of-culture-blocks/" title="MPA Capstone Project To Assess Impact Of Culture Blocks">
          MPA Capstone Project To Assess Impact Of Culture Blocks
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         February 06, 2019 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          The Arts &amp; Science Council's Culture Blocks program brings arts, science and history experiences into neighborhoods – at libraries, parks, recreation centers, and other community spaces. Through the UNC Charlotte Master of Public Administration capstone project, MPA student researchers are helping the ASC and their community partners better measure and understand the impact of the program.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
      <!-- .post -->
      <div class="story teaching-advising-section landscape-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2018/06/Copy-of-Preserving-Memory-6-600x386.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/preserving-memory-study-of-cemeteries-role-in-communities-takes-global-approach/" title="Preserving Memory: Study of Cemeteries' Role In Communities Takes Global Approach">
          Preserving Memory: Study of Cemeteries' Role In Communities Takes Global Approach
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         July 06, 2018 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/cmauk/" title="Posts by Caitlin Mauk">
          Caitlin Mauk
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          UNC Charlotte historian Aaron Shapiro thinks deeply about the impact of society’s resting places and the importance of protecting and understanding them. In his co-teaching of a history class called “Preserving Memory in the Digital Age,” Shapiro strives to help students broaden their perspectives on cemeteries and their surrounding communities, through in-depth research and class work.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
      <!-- .post -->
      <div class="more">
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/teaching-and-advising/" title="Teaching &amp; Advising Archives">
        More
        <em>
         TEACHING &amp; ADVISING
        </em>
        »
       </a>
      </div>
      <!-- .more -->
     </div>
     <!-- .section-box -->
    </div>
   </div>
   <div class="widget widget_section_listing" id="section_listing-26">
    <div class="wscontrol section-listing-control" id="section-listing-control-15">
     <div class="section-box in-memoriam-section portrait-image">
      <h2>
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/memoriam/" title="IN MEMORIAM Archives">
        IN MEMORIAM
       </a>
      </h2>
      <div class="story in-memoriam-section portrait-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2018/12/Sue-Spaulding-1-400x600.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/in-time-of-loss-colleagues-reflect-on-impact-of-retired-faculty-member/" title="In Time of Loss, Colleagues Reflect On Impact of Retired Faculty Member">
          In Time of Loss, Colleagues Reflect On Impact of Retired Faculty Member
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         December 06, 2018 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          Sue Spaulding, long-time member of the Department of Psychology at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte, died suddenly on December 5, 2018. An avid and fearless traveler, she was doing what she loved most—cruising the sunny tropics. She was hired as Lab Director in 1993 and served the department in a variety of roles until her retirement in 2014.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
      <!-- .post -->
      <div class="story in-memoriam-section portrait-image listing post-15726 post type-post status-publish format-standard has-post-thumbnail hentry category-college-publications">
       <div class="image" style="background-image:url('https://exchange.uncc.edu/wp-content/uploads/sites/14/2018/12/in-memoriam.jpg')" title="Featured Image">
       </div>
       <!-- .image -->
       <div class="details">
        <h3>
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/retired-psychology-faculty-chair-remembered/" title="Retired Psychology Founding Chair Remembered">
          Retired Psychology Founding Chair Remembered
         </a>
        </h3>
        <div class="byline">
         December 06, 2018 by
         <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/author/lrobers2/" title="Posts by Lynn Roberson">
          Lynn Roberson
         </a>
        </div>
        <div class="description">
         <div class="excerpt">
          Dr. Louis Diamant (Lou), professor emeritus at the University of North Carolina at Charlotte, died at home in Charlotte on November 23, 2018. In 1963, when the University was still Charlotte College and consisted of only two buildings, Diamant became the founding chairperson of the Psychology Department.
         </div>
        </div>
        <!-- .description -->
       </div>
       <!-- .details -->
      </div>
      <!-- .post -->
      <div class="more">
       <a href="https://exchange.uncc.edu/section/memoriam/" title="In Memoriam Archives">
        More
        <em>
         IN MEMORIAM
        </em>
        »
       </a>
      </div>
      <!-- .more -->
     </div>
     <!-- .section-box -->
    </div>
